# Enterprise OS Hardening Strategy

## Linux Hardening Controls

The following enterprise hardening measures were recommended:

- Disable root SSH login
- Enforce multi-factor authentication (MFA)
- Implement Fail2Ban for brute-force mitigation
- Apply password complexity and rotation policies
- Restrict administrative privileges using least privilege principles
- Disable unused services and ports
- Configure centralised syslog forwarding
- Enable auditd logging
- Apply kernel hardening configurations
- Deploy AppArmor or SELinux enforcement

---

